(8) Laboratory hour means a minimum of fifty minutes of educational
activity on campus or off campus in which students conduct experiments, perfect
skills, or practice procedures under the direction of a qualified instructor;

(13) Full-time equivalent student enrollment total means
the total of full-time equivalent students enrolled in a community college
in any fiscal year;

(16) Academic support course means a general education academic
course offering which may be necessary to support an applied technology or
occupational program;

(22) Reimbursable educational unit total means the total
of all reimbursable educational units accumulated in a community college area
in any fiscal year;

(23) Special instructional term means any term which is less
than fifteen weeks for community colleges using semesters or ten weeks for
community colleges using quarters;

(24) Statewide reimbursable full-time equivalent total means
the total of all reimbursable full-time equivalents accumulated statewide
for the community college in any fiscal year;
